name: Kebokeboan
description: Kebo-keboan are a ritual performed by the Banyuwangi (East Java - Indonesia) community as a form of gratitude for the abundant harvest and also as a prayer so that the next year's harvest will be good.  Kebo (buffalo) is an animal that is closely related to agricultural culture, it helps farmers in cultivating their fields.  Kebo-keboan is performed by wearing a buffalo costume and acting like a buffalo in the fields.
